<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="public-n">public <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pʌblɪk/    美 /'pʌblɪk/  </p>
<p>[与the连用]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>公众；民众：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The news shocked the public, leading to great concern about students’ safety at school.
这则消息使公众感到震惊，同时引起人们对学生在校安全的极大关注。</p><footer>2010 重庆</footer></div>

<p>注: the public作主语时，如表示整体，谓语动词用单数形式；如表示各个成员，谓语动词用复数形式。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="in-public">in public</h3>
<p>1.<strong>当众；公开地【反:in private】：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t laugh or talk loudly in public. It’s bad manners.
不要在公共场合大声说笑，这样不礼貌。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>publicity /pʌb'lɪsəti/ n [U] <br />
publicly /'pʌblɪkli/ adv   </p>
<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>His daughter is always shy <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ public and she never dares to make a speech to the public.  （2001 上海春改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. in  </p></div>